# A14 Charge Keeper

A lightweight command-line tool for managing battery charging limits on supported Linux laptops.

## Supported Hardware
- ASUS TUF A14 and compatible models
- ThinkPad laptops with battery threshold support
- Other laptops with Linux kernel sysfs battery control

## Quick Start
1. Check hardware support: `check-support`
2. Set battery limit: `sudo a14-charge-keeper set 80`
3. Make permanent: `sudo a14-charge-keeper persist 80`

## Commands
- `set <20-100>`: Set charge threshold
- `status`: Show current status
- `persist <20-100>`: Enable auto-reapply on boot/resume
- `clear`: Reset to 100% and disable auto-reapply
- `verify <20-100>`: Verify current setting

## Environment Variables
- `BAT_NAME`: Override battery device name (default: BAT0)

## Version
0.3.0

